{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandate robust safety posts at bus stops to prevent fatal accidents",
        "additional_details": "Too many lives are lost while people are standing at bus stops. People are waiting static at the side of busy roads. My son was trapped inside a bus stop shelter when a lorry hit him, he had nowhere to run. Protection posts could have saved his life. Others have died in the same way and I believe that this could have been avoided. We want to make it legislation that all relevant authorities must install mandatory posts at every bus stop to protect our children and citizens.",
        "background": "My son Logan's death highlights the need for bus stop safety. We believe our loss and others affected by bus stop deaths could have been avoided by installing crash bollards. We want urgent action to prioritise pedestrian safety at stops, installing bollard and posts to prevent vehicle collisions.\r\n",
